STUDIES
ON
NEUTRON
ACTIVATION
ANALYSIS
FOR
THE
MEASUREMENT
OF
SODIUM
IN
NAILS
AS
A
SCREENING
TEST
FOR
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
THE
PRESENT
STUDY
POINTS
OUT
THE
SIMPLICITY
AND
EASE
OF
USING
FINGERNAILS
AND
TOENAILS
TO
MEASURE
ELECTROLYTE
LEVELS
AS
A
TEST
FOR
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
PROCEDURES
AND
VARIOUS
EFFECTS
ON
THE
RANGES
OF
VALUES
FOR
DIFFERENT
CATEGORIES
OF
HEALTHY
AND
DISEASED
SUBJECTS
ARE
DISCUSSED
AND
THE
LIMITATIONS
OF
THE
METHOD
ARE
INDICATED
